The paper deals with random walks on high dimensional simplicial complexes, which are objects studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of colorful expansion, which is introduced in the paper, is a new notion of high dimensional combinatorial expansion, which falls under the category of spectral graph theory (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also discusses the convergence of the random walk, which involves analyzing the eigenvalues of matrices, a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
